SIMPLE: extractor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extractor
<hw>Ex*tract"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, extracts</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>
<def>A forceps or instrument for extracting substances.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Breech-loading Firearms)</fld> <def>A device for
withdrawing a cartridge or spent cartridge shell from the chamber of the
barrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A centrifugal drying machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Apiculture)</fld> <def>A machine for clearing combs
of honey; also, a device for rendering wax.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extradictionary</ent>⟦br⟧
